/************************/
Step to creare package.json
/************************/
*NodeJs Must be installed
> Navigate to the folder using cmd/terminal
> type 'npm init'
> Answer all question
> type 'yes'

/************************/
Step to install packages
/************************/
localpackage
> Navigate to the folder using cmd/terminal
> npm install <packagename>/ npm i <packagename>

globalpackage
**No spacific folder
(create,build,test,deploy)
>Window
=> run your can admin
=> npm i -g <packagename>

Mac/Linux
> Open your terminal
> sudo npm i -g <packagename>

sudo npm i -g @aakashdeveloper/create-node-app

/////////////////////////////
**Very First When we get appliication form any one
/////////////////////////////
> Navigate to the folder using cmd/terminal
> npm install
(it will install all dependeices from package.json)


npm i zone.js --save


/************************/
Step to setup angular appliication
/************************/
Window
(one time)
> run your cmd as admin
> start => search(cmd)=> rightclick=> run as adminstrator
> npm i -g @angular/cli

(every application)
> Navigate to the folder using cmd/terminal
> ng new <appliication name>(myapp)
> cd myapp
> npm start
> http://localhost:4200(open in browser)

Mac/Linux
(one time)
> open your terminal
> sudo npm i -g @angular/cli

(every application)
> Navigate to the folder using cmd/terminal
> ng new <appliication name>(myapp)
> cd myapp
> npm start
> http://localhost:4200(open in browser)


///
To Change port number
///
> ng serve --port 8900

Angular is a frontend framework which help to build single page application with
Component based structure using typescript


/*****************
Building Block
*****************/
Component => one page act like component (HTML, CSS, Logic)
Pipe=> Run time data change
Service => To connect with thrid part or any external agent(dependeicy injection)
Directive => Small part of page(reusable)
Routing => To handle multiple page
Module=> To declare all the things

*****
> One Main Module
> One Main Component
*****

